Texas, remember the importance of social distancing. If you must go out, avoid public spaces and keep your distance from others (at least 6 feet). If we continue to follow valuable public health guidance, fewer of our friends & family will be affected by COVID-19. #StayHomeTexas

Common symptoms of #COVID19 are fever, dry cough, & shortness of breath. If you have mild symptoms, call your doctor & #StayHome. If you develop serious symptoms, such as trouble breathing, pressure in the chest, or bluish lips or face, call your doctor & seek care immediately.

Los síntomas comunes de #COVID19 son fiebre, tos seca y dificultad para respirar. Si tiene síntomas leves, llame a su médico y quedate en casa. Si desarrolla síntomas graves, como dificultad para respirar o presión en el pecho, busque atención médica de inmediato. #StayHome

Before social distancing, each person with #COVID19 spread the virus to 2.5 more people. At that pace, most would get it, and many more people would die. But we can slow the spread. That’s why we all #StayHome. #ApartTogether we slow coronavirus.

Antes del distanciamiento social, cada persona con #COVID19 transmitió el virus a 2.5 personas.A ese ritmo, muchas personas se contagiarían, y muchas personas morirían.Pero podemos retrasar la propagación.Por eso todos quedemonos en casa y paremos el Coronavirus.#ApartTogether

COVID-19 TISD Update: Tornillo Learning Community, The Coyote Community Park is closed until further notice as specified by new local government ordinance. Let’s help stop the spread! #TISDProud

Informe Actual COVID-19: El parque de la comunidad de Tornillo estara cerrado al publico hasta nueva orden del condado.

Practice Social Distancing

To avoid the spread of COVID-19 in our community, practice social distancing:
• Avoid going out in public
• When in public, keep six feet of distance between you and others
• Follow guidance provided by local and state officials.
Get more information at https://texas.gov/covid19
#covid19 #texasstrong #stayhome

Practica el distanciamiento social

Para prevenir la propagación de COVID-19 en nuestra comunidad, practique el distanciamiento social:
• Evite salir en público
• Cuando esté en público, mantenga una distancia de seis pies entre usted y los demás.
• Seguir las recomendaciones de los funcionarios locales y estatales.
Obtenga más información en https://texas.gov/covid19
#covid19 #texasfuerte #quedateencasa

Tocando is feeling thankful.
February 11 at 5:20 PM ·

Tocando expanded to include programming in Tornillo, Texas in January 2020. Funding by the NAMM Foundation was instrumental in the expansion. Yesterday the Executive Director of the NAMM Foundation visited the program, met the Elementary and Intermediate School Principals, Administration of the Tornillo Independent School District, two TISD Board Members, our wonderful Program Directors/Teaching Artists in Tornillo and the Tocando program at Guillen! Thank you TISD for making NAMM Foundation feel very welcome and a part of Team Tocando! #nammfoundation #tisd #music #epso #tocando

- Meals must be eaten on site

post_text: The Tornillo ISD has not had any confirmed threats made to its schools. We are in normal operation and continue to take all safety measures to assure our schools continue to be safe. We ask the help from our community to contact law enforcement immediately should a threat be made to our schools/individuals. We take every threat seriously and will act accordingly so those individuals causing unnecessary panic to be disciplined and law enforcement to take action that may result in a misdemeanor or felony.

We are very excited to announce that our fifth Parent ELL Night will be hosted at Tornillo High School on Wednesday, November 15, 2017 from 5:00 to 7:00 pm.

This is another great opportunity to inform our ELL parents about the benefits of our Bilingual/ESL program as well as strategies that can be used at home to help their kids to be successful in school!

The invitation is opened to ALL the ELL parents in the district. There will be sessions aimed to Elementary/Intermediate and Junior High/High School parents.

Community Wide pep rally!
text:
MON, NOV 7, 2016
Community Wide pep rally!

post_text:
The Tornillo High School Student Council is hosting a community-wide Pep Rally at 6 pm on Monday, Nov. 7, in the main gym at the high school. Everyone is invited to come out and meet our high school and junior high school boys and girls basketball teams, and our tennis teams. In addition, we will be honoring the boys cross country team which has advanced to state level competition. Way to go, Coyotes!

In addition, you will get to meet the girls who will be playing in our first Tornillo High School Powder Puff football game, which is scheduled for next Friday, Nov. 11, at 7 pm at the football field.

We will also have Clash of the Classes competitions, a performance by the cheerleaders, and learn a new cheer.

Lets show our coyote pride and show our hardworking athletes that the Tornillo community is behind them!

post_text: On Friday night our girls basketball team was able to beat Presidio High school to win the Districts 4-3A title. The Lady Coyotes went into Friday night’s game with an undefeated district record. With 2 minutes left in the game Presidio pulled within 8 points but the Lady Coyotes were able maintain the lead and the victory. This is the Lady Coyotes first district championship in over ten years. Congratulations Lady Coyotes!

TISD WEATHER UPDATE:

The rain has not interrupted classes today. However, we continue to monitor the weather to assess the safety of our students and employees.

Our campuses are experiencing isolated roof leaks, which are being addressed by the TISD Maintenance Department. These leaks are not uncommon in our older buildings, but everything is being done to help remedy the situation.

Please check back for further updates. Information will be shared via the TISD website www.tisd.us and our social media outlets.

Stay warm, stay dry and stay safe Tornillo.

Elementary School - 11:30 AM Release 765-3100
Intermediate School - 11:30 AM Release 765-3300
Junior High School - 12:00 PM Release 765-3400
